{"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/DBusProxy","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/DBusProxy\/AsyncInitableProtocol-Implementations"]]},"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"patch":0,"minor":3},"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/gio\/dbusproxy\/initasync(iopriority:cancellable:callback:userdata:)"]}],"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"tokens":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"initAsync"},{"text":"(","kind":"text"},{"text":"ioPriority","kind":"externalParam"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"Int","preciseIdentifier":"s:Si"},{"text":", ","kind":"text"},{"text":"cancellable","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:3GIO14CancellableRefV","kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"CancellableRef","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/CancellableRef"},{"text":"? = nil, ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"callback"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"c:@T@GAsyncReadyCallback","text":"GAsyncReadyCallback"},{"text":"? = nil, ","kind":"text"},{"text":"userData","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"text":"gpointer","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"c:gtypes.h@T@gpointer"},{"text":"? = nil)","kind":"text"}],"platforms":["macOS"],"languages":["swift"]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"content":[{"text":"Discussion","type":"heading","level":2,"anchor":"discussion"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This method is intended for language bindings. If writing in C,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"code":"g_async_initable_new_async()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" should typically be used instead."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"When the initialization is finished, "},{"code":"callback","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" will be called. You can","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"then call ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_async_initable_init_finish()"},{"text":" to get the result of the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"initialization."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Implementations may also support cancellation. If "},{"code":"cancellable","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" is not"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"nil"},{"type":"text","text":", then initialization can be cancelled by triggering the cancellable"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"object from another thread. If the operation was cancelled, the error","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"cancelled"},{"type":"text","text":" will be returned. If "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"cancellable"},{"type":"text","text":" is not "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"nil"},{"type":"text","text":", and"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"the object doesn’t support cancellable initialization, the error","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"notSupported"},{"text":" will be returned.","type":"text"}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"As with "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/Initable"},{"text":", if the object is not initialized, or initialization","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"returns with an error, then all operations on the object except","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"code":"g_object_ref()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" and ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_object_unref()"},{"text":" are considered to be invalid, and","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"have undefined behaviour. They will often fail with "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_critical()"},{"type":"text","text":" or"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_warning()"},{"text":", but this must not be relied on.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Callers should not assume that a class which implements "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/AsyncInitable","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" can","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"be initialized multiple times; for more information, see "},{"code":"g_initable_init()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":".","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"If a class explicitly supports being initialized multiple times,","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"implementation requires yielding all subsequent calls to "},{"code":"init_async()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" on the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"results of the first call."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"For classes that also support the "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/Initable","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" interface, the default"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"implementation of this method will run the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_initable_init()"},{"type":"text","text":" function"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"in a thread, so if you want to support asynchronous initialization via","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"threads, just implement the "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/AsyncInitable"},{"type":"text","text":" interface without overriding"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"any interface methods."}],"type":"paragraph"}],"kind":"content"}],"sections":[],"abstract":[{"text":"Starts asynchronous initialization of the object implementing the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"interface. This must be done before any 